The Context Principle

	Philosophy

		-
			The context principle is the principle that different sets of moral and ethical
			principles and priorities may apply differently depending on the context in which they
			are applied.
		-

	Principles

		The Context Fallacy

			-
				The context fallacy is the perception that if a given moral or ethical principle or
				priority is not effective in all contexts then said principle or priority must be
				inherently contradictory or hypocritical.
